{"title_page": "General Tire 150 (Charlotte)", "text_new": "{{Infobox motor race\n|Race title = General Tire 150\n|Logo = [[File:General Tire 150 Charlotte.svg|150px]]\n|Track map = Lowe's Motor Speedway.svg\n|Series long = [[ARCA Menards Series]]\n|Series short = AMS\n|Venue = [[Charlotte Motor Speedway]]\n|Location = [[Concord, North Carolina]]\n|Sponsor = [[General Tire]]\n|First race = 1996\n|Last race = \n|Distance = {{convert|150.0|mi|km|abbr=on}}\n|Laps = 100\n|Duration = \n|Previous names = '''ADG EasyCare 100''' (1996)<br>'''ADG Easy Care Certified 100''' (1997)<br>'''EasyCare Vehicle Service Contracts 100''' (1998-2002)<br>'''ADG 100 presented by EasyCare''' (2003)<br>'''Quaker Steak & Lube 100''' (2004)\n|Most wins driver = [[Frank Kimmel]] (3)\n|Most wins team = Clement Racing (3)\n|Most wins manufacturer = [[Ford]] (6)\n|Length mi = 1.5\n|Turns = 4\n}}\n\nThe '''General Tire 150''' is a {{convert|150|mi|km|adj=on}} annual [[ARCA Menards Series]] race held at [[Charlotte Motor Speedway]] in [[Concord, North Carolina]]. The inaugural event was held on May 18, 1996 and was won by [[Tim Steele (racing driver)|Tim Steele]]. The race was originally held during the month of May between 1996 and 2004, after which it was removed from the calendar. The race returned to the series in 2018 and has remained since.\n\n==History==\n\nARCA previously ran at Charlotte Motor Speedway from 1996 to 2004. In 1996 and 1997, the series ran three times at the speedway: twice in May and once in either late September or early October. In 1998, the [[General Tire 150 (Charlotte)#Former middle race|middle race]] was dropped, leaving just one spring race and [[General Tire 150 (Charlotte)#Former fall race|one fall race]]. For 2004, the fall race was dropped, before the track was dropped altogether for the 2005 season.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.racing-reference.info/tracks/Charlotte_Motor_Speedway|title=Charlotte Motor Speedway|work=Racing-reference.info|publisher=[[NASCAR]]|accessdate=March 30, 2020}}</ref>\n\n==Past winners==\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"font-size: 95%;\"\n|-\n! rowspan=\"2\"|Year\n! rowspan=\"2\"|Date\n! rowspan=\"2\"|{{Tooltip|No.|Car number}}\n! rowspan=\"2\"|Driver\n! rowspan=\"2\"|Team\n! rowspan=\"2\"|Manufacturer\n! colspan=\"2\"|Race Distance\n! rowspan=\"2\"|Race Time\n! rowspan=\"2\"|Average Speed<br />(mph)\n! rowspan=\"2\"|Report\n|-\n! Laps\n! Miles (km)\n|-\n| 1996\n| May 18\n|align=\"center\"|16\n| [[Tim Steele (racing driver)|Tim Steele]]\n| [[Steele Racing]]\n| [[Ford]]\n|align=\"center\"|67\n|align=\"center\"|100.5 (161.739)\n|align=\"center\"|0:54:19\n|align=\"center\"|111.016\n| [https://www.racing-reference.info/race/1996_ADG_EasyCare_100/A Report]\n|-\n| 1997\n| May 17\n|align=\"center\"|66\n| [[Mark Thompson (racing driver)|Mark Thompson]]\n| Mike Brandt\n| [[Ford]]\n|align=\"center\"|67\n|align=\"center\"|100.5 (161.739)\n|align=\"center\"|0:48:50\n|align=\"center\"|123.481\n| [https://www.racing-reference.info/race/1997_EasyCare_Certified_100/A Report]\n|-\n| 1998\n| May 16\n|align=\"center\"|46\n| [[Frank Kimmel]]\n| Clement Racing\n| [[Chevrolet]]\n|align=\"center\"|67\n|align=\"center\"|100.5 (161.739)\n|align=\"center\"|0:53:36\n|align=\"center\"|112.500\n| [https://www.racing-reference.info/race/1998_EasyCare_Vehicle_Services_Contracts_100/A Report]\n|-\n| 1999\n| May 22\n|align=\"center\"|58\n| [[Mario Gosselin (racing driver)|Mario Gosselin]]\n| [[Wings Racing]]\n| [[Chevrolet]]\n|align=\"center\"|63*\n|align=\"center\"|94.5 (152.083)\n|align=\"center\"|0:56:21\n|align=\"center\"|100.621\n| [https://www.racing-reference.info/race/1999_EasyCare_Vehicle_Services_Contracts_100_(May)/A Report]\n|-\n| 2000\n| May 20\n|align=\"center\"|99\n| [[Lyndon Amick]]\n| [[Ken Schrader Racing]]\n| [[Pontiac]]\n|align=\"center\"|67\n|align=\"center\"|100.5 (161.739)\n|align=\"center\"|0:54:01\n|align=\"center\"|111.632\n| [https://www.racing-reference.info/race/2000_EasyCare_Vehicle_Services_Contracts_